      "writtenOn": "2018-06-07T17:41:06Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is not about prefixes. There may be a PACKAGE named as some of visible root. An example is this list of packages (in chrome-infra-auth-dev):\n\n  infra/tools/cipd\n  infra/tools/cipd/linux-amd64\n  infra/tools/cipd/linux-mac64\n  ...\n\nHere infra/tools/cipd is both a package and a prefix. This is allowed.\n\nNow imagine infra/tools/... is not readable, but infra/tools/cipd is, and the caller is listing infra/tools. In this case visibleRoots will be [\"infra/tools/cipd\"]. But ListPackages(\"infra/tools/cipd\") will return only [\"infra/tools/cipd/linux-amd64\", \"infra/tools/cipd/linux-mac64\", ...] and the package \"infra/tools/cipd\" itself will be lost.",
